It comprises 11 academic departments naming Klingler College of Arts & Sciences, College of Business Administration, Diederich College of Communication, School of Dentistry, College of Education, Opus College of Engineering, Graduate School, Graduate School of Management, College of Health Sciences, Law School and College of Nursing.

College_Heading: University of Nevada: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships

College_Heading: Harding University: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Harding University was founded in 1924 when two junior colleges, Arkansas Christian College and Harper College joined institutions to form a full-fledged senior university. It was granted the university status by the board of trustees in 1979 and is located in the town of Searcy, Ark. It is a private Christian Institute with a close connection to churches and wishes to spread education and philosophy among its students through consistency with Christian ideals.

College_Heading: Abilene Christian University [ACU]: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Abilene Christian University (ACU) is a private Christian University in Abilene, Texas. It was originally known as Children's Classical Institute when established in 1906. ACU aims in transforming their students into the likeness of Jesus and creates leaders who think critically, globally,missionally through distinctive and innovative programs that provide a unique, Christ oriented experience that attracts students into the community. The university is accredited by The Southern Association of colleges and schools commissions on colleges to award associate, baccalaureate, masters and doctoral degrees, making it one of the popular Christian Universities to study in the US.

College_Heading: Texas Woman’s University [TWU], USA: Ranking, Programs, Application Deadlines, Admission, Fees, Scholarships
College_Summary: Texas Woman’s University is a public, co-ed university established in 1901 as the state’s only public university for educating women. As the name suggests, Texas Woman's University was entirely women oriented since its inception until 1994. It has campuses in Denton, Dallas and Houston. The university has a total enrollment of 15,000 students including around 5,200 graduate students. It is considered to have one of the most diverse student bodies in the country making it a preferred destination for higher education in US. It had an acceptance rate of 93% in fall 2022, indicating towards a less selective admission policy.

College_Summary: University of Mary Hardin Baylor is a renowned private Christian University that was established in 1845 and is located in Belton, Texas. College_Heading: University of Charleston [UC], USA: Ranking, Courses, Admission, Tuition Fee, Scholarships
College_Summary: Founded in 1888 as the Barboursville Seminary, University of Charleston got its name in 1978. It is a private university located on the banks of Kanawha River in Charleston, West Virginia. The university also has its campus in Beckley, West Virginia. The institution is accredited by The Higher Learning Commission. It had a total enrollment of 2,620 students out of which 1,882 undergraduates and 738 graduate students. International students representing over 44 countries are a part of the university which is a renowned name for higher education in US.

College_Heading: Witten Herdecke University Germany- Rankings, Campus, Accommodation, Programs, Admissions, Cost of Attendance and Scholarships

UW/H offers limited courses at UG, PG, and doctoral- level in several academic areas like management and economics, psychology, nursing science, medicine and dentistry. College_Heading: Southwestern University [SU]: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Southwestern University is a private independent institute with religious affiliation from Christian-Methodist. With a flexible curriculum, cutting edge research, experiential learning, modern ways of critical evaluation and thinking, and real-world application; SU, as it is also called, is poised in equipping students from multiple perspectives. Admission at Southwestern University is averagely selective with an acceptance rate between 40% to 50%. In the academic year 2023, the university received 4,578 applications for undergraduate admissions. Out of the total application received, only 49% were given a place and 16% of them were enrolled. About 45% of male and 53% of female students were accepted by the university.

College_Summary: Millsaps College is one of the top private liberal arts colleges in the U.S. Established in 1890, it is affiliated with Christian-Methodist. It has an urban campus spread across 100 acres of land in the heart of Jackson, Mississippi. About 750 students are enrolled in the college including 57% of the undergraduate students from 26 states and international students from 23 countries for higher education in US. College_Heading: Linfield College, USA: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: Founded in 1858, Linfield College is a private, co-educational institution located in McMinnville, Oregon, USA. It has two campuses and the other campus at Portland houses the Linfield-Good Samaritan School of Nursing offering nursing programs to non-traditional and adult students to complete their bachelor’s degree. The school changed its name to Linfield University in July with a College of Arts and Sciences, School of Business and School of Nursing. The college primarily offers undergraduate degrees with over 50 majors and 2 master’s degrees for higher education in US. Linfield Online and Continuing Education offers fully online programs to working adults. The institution is accredited by the Northwest Commission on Colleges and Universities.

College_Heading: First Nations University [FNUniv] of Canada: Rankings, Courses, Admissions, Tuition Fee, Cost of Attendance & Scholarships
College_Summary: The First Nations University of Canada was established in 1976 as Saskatchewan Indian Federated College and is presently a federated college of the University of Regina. Due to this reason, admissions and other academic activities at the institute are conducted as per the guidelines of its parent university. The institute is a renowned higher education institute of Canada, specialized in offering indigenous knowledge and is highly respectful of diverse cultural beliefs.

College_Summary: HEC Montreal is the 2nd best business school affiliated with the University of Montreal in Canada. The school shares 117 years of experience, being the first ever Management Schools in Canada. You can select from 150 programs at HEC Montreal ranging from Bachelor's, Master’s and PhD. HEC Montreal offers education to 13,420 students, including 3,676 international applicants from 145 countries.
